"{\"uid\": \"ocregister.com-2024-07-30-kaylee-mckeown-still-rules-the-olympic-backstroke-beating-regan-smith-in-womens-100-meters\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"e-Edition  Get the latest news delivered daily!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 47, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the latest news delivered daily!\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 87, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"e-Edition  Trending:  By PAUL NEWBERRY  NANTERRE, France (AP) - Kaylee McKeown still rules the women's Olympic backstroke.\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 114, \"end\": 118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_(bakery)\", \"score\": 0.9418719497533347, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"PAUL\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_(bakery)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_(bakery)\"}, {\"begin\": 119, \"end\": 127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newberry_Library\", \"score\": 0.9999667335167993, \"rank\": 3.326758928841934e-05, \"text\": \"NEWBERRY\", \"types\": [\"Q7075\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newberry_Library\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newberry_Library\"}, {\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"score\": 0.9998562966001483, \"rank\": 0.00014291964055458404, \"text\": \"NANTERRE\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\"}, {\"begin\": 139, \"end\": 145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9741413110758775, \"rank\": 0.02651343192831503, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9985105295926205, \"rank\": 0.0014916922388611745, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian knocked off world-record holder Regan Smith of the United States in the 100 back on Tuesday night, defending the title she won at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 213, \"end\": 227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.870346892653064e-14, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.460027240766817e-30, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.999999292897678, \"rank\": 4.107264203645074e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith, who\\u00a0broke McKeown's world mark\\u00a0with a time of 57.13 seconds at the U.S. trials last month, led at the turn but could not hold off the hard-charging Aussie, who defended the title she won in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 573, \"end\": 578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999936022052, \"rank\": 6.397801322068256e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She is an absolutely incredible racer and she knows what to do when it matters,\\\" Smith said.\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I am really proud of myself.\\\"\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown surged to the front about halfway through the return lap and reached for the wall in 57.33, winning by a relatively comfortable margin over Smith's finish of 57.66.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The nerves were definitely there but I just reminded myself it's a pool in a different venue and I train every single day of my life,\\\" McKeown said.\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. also grabbed the bronze as Katharine Berkoff touched third in 57.98.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katharine Berkoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith reached over the lane rope to congratulate McKeown, but this one had to sting.\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old Minnesota native appeared to be in top form after her performance and primed to win the first gold medal of her career.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\", \"score\": 0.987050589356223, \"rank\": 0.012408250933629567, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, it was McKeown capturing the third individual gold of her career and fourth gold overall.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She swept the backstroke events in Tokyo and also claimed a relay gold.\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999936022052, \"rank\": 6.397801322068256e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's one race at a time,\\\" McKeown said.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have checked off three boxes so far and there is a few more to go.\\\"\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniel Wiffen won Ireland's first gold medal in swimming since scandal-plagued Michelle Smith finished first in three events at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9419946507817375, \"rank\": 0.05579356802432567, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1717, \"end\": 1725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9146560054592013, \"rank\": 0.09330232085637566, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1770, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6540562353567979e-18, \"text\": \"1996 Atlanta Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6309763809094087e-18, \"text\": \"Atlanta Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen surged past Italy's Gregorio Paltrinieri on the final lap, looking as fresh as he did at the beginning of the grueling race.\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9944167957490915, \"rank\": 0.005607338935811247, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gregorio Paltrinieri\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen won in 7 minutes, 38.19 seconds, climbing on the lane ropes to hold one finger skyward.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 2021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Defending Olympic champion Bobby Finke of the U.S. also came on strong in what was essentially a three-man race, also passing Paltrinieri to take the silver in 7:38.75.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2049, \"end\": 2060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze went to the Italian, who posted a time of 7:39.38.\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.999997566223334, \"rank\": 2.37756580592931e-06, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was another dazzling performance by an Irish swimmer, on the heels of\\u00a0Mona McSharry grabbing a bronze in the 100 breaststroke\\u00a0the previous night.\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2297, \"end\": 2302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.7304081248292681, \"rank\": 0.23645927711893294, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 2328, \"end\": 2341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mona McSharry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until these Olympics, the country's swimming history was essentially confined to Smith, who surprisingly claimed three golds and a bronze in 1996 amid suspicions she was doping.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She later received a doping ban that essentially ended her career, but she kept her medals.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain defended their title in the men's 4x-200 freestyle relay, holding off the United States and Australia.\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2676, \"end\": 2683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999832421757553, \"rank\": 1.6758038295819614e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2758, \"end\": 2771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.999999292897678, \"rank\": 4.107264203645074e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2776, \"end\": 2785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9938819693062176, \"rank\": 0.006098322739884648, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team of James Guy, Tom Dean, Matthew Richards and Duncan Scott - the same foursome that captured gold in Tokyo three years ago - finished in 6:59.43.\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2800, \"end\": 2809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Guy_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9824541369257855, \"rank\": 0.017851239669423005, \"text\": \"James Guy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Guy_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Guy_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9999936593363623, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9913273362707572, \"rank\": 0.004373974849644039, \"text\": \"Duncan Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999936022052, \"rank\": 6.397801322068256e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only difference from the last Olympics was Dean took the leadoff, with Guy going second.\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 3035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2990, \"end\": 2994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.9999909244418462, \"rank\": 6.39620073250541e-06, \"text\": \"Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was good enough for another gold, Britain's first swimming victory of the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3073, \"end\": 3080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999832421757553, \"rank\": 1.6758038295819614e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luke Hobson, Carson Foster, Drew Kibler and Kieran Smith gained a bit of redemption for the Americans with a silver medal in 7:00.78, making up for a disappointing fourth-place showing at the last Olympics.\", \"from\": 3127, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3127, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel_of_Luke\", \"score\": 0.682337404471634, \"rank\": 0.2944317210964922, \"text\": \"Luke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel_of_Luke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel_of_Luke\"}, {\"begin\": 3132, \"end\": 3138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Hobson\", \"score\": 0.9928726782535745, \"rank\": 0.0071571209897984215, \"text\": \"Hobson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Hobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Hobson\"}, {\"begin\": 3140, \"end\": 3153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carson Foster\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\"}, {\"begin\": 3155, \"end\": 3166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Kibler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drew Kibler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Kibler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Kibler\"}, {\"begin\": 3171, \"end\": 3183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kieran Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maximillian Giuliani, Flynn Southam, Elijah Winnington and Thomas Neill earned the bronze for Australia in 7:01.98.\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3357, \"end\": 3362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Errol_Flynn\", \"score\": 0.9999999998453859, \"rank\": 1.5481701857157463e-10, \"text\": \"Flynn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Errol_Flynn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Errol_Flynn\"}, {\"begin\": 3363, \"end\": 3370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmedia_Network\", \"score\": 0.9999999979099812, \"rank\": 2.08997608776385e-09, \"text\": \"Southam\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmedia_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmedia_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 3372, \"end\": 3389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah_Winnington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elijah Winnington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah_Winnington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah_Winnington\"}, {\"begin\": 3394, \"end\": 3406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Neill_(insurance_executive)\", \"score\": 0.9999608783004326, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Neill\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Neill_(insurance_executive)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Neill_(insurance_executive)\"}, {\"begin\": 3429, \"end\": 3438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9938819693062176, \"rank\": 0.006098322739884648, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French star L\\u00e9on Marchand\\u00a0had a very busy day, advancing to the final in both the 200 butterfly and 200 breaststroke.\", \"from\": 3452, \"to\": 3569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3452, \"end\": 3458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6628401407398442, \"rank\": 0.3726912089406954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3464, \"end\": 3477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999997803538704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He posted a time of 1:53.50 in the fly semis, trailing only defending Olympic champion and world-record holder Krist\\u00f3f Mil\\u00e1k of Hungary (1.52.72).\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3682, \"end\": 3695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krist\\u00f3f_Mil\\u00e1k\", \"score\": 0.9999999973315425, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Krist\\u00f3f Mil\\u00e1k\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krist\\u00f3f_Mil\\u00e1k\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krist\\u00f3f_Mil\\u00e1k\"}, {\"begin\": 3699, \"end\": 3706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9732125978681319, \"rank\": 0.027524717791462525, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand was faster than everyone in the breaststroke round, posting a time of 2:08.11 with another raucous crowd at La Defense Arena cheering him on.\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand will have to double up one more time in the finals Wednesday, looking to add to the gold he earned in the 400 individual medley.\", \"from\": 3870, \"to\": 4007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 MediaNews Group\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4026, \"end\": 4041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"MediaNews Group\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\"}]}]}"